2.9.3 added comments, not finished with adding weeknumbers
moved files from proefexamen to examen_proef

Add tests, data, and new Python scripts for analysis
This commit introduces several new files, including test data files (`test.txt`, `namen.txt`, `verbruik.txt`, `landen.txt`) and multiple Python scripts for object-oriented examples and data processing. Key updates include aggregating usage data for countries, creating class structures with special methods, and adding test utilities for analysis.

Update project_management.xlsx in examen_pm folder
Modified project_management.xlsx to reflect necessary changes. Ensure the file is up-to-date for accurate project management tracking.

Add theorie.txt with exam preparation content
This commit introduces a new file, theorie.txt, containing answers to questions and structured information for exam preparation. It includes multiple-choice responses, daily stand-up topics, and issue-related details for better organization.

Add SFTP functionality and automated file processing
Introduced SFTP client and file processing pipeline in `main.py` to facilitate connecting to remote hosts, downloading files, and processing data. Simplified error handling and path management in `connect_to_PLC.py`. Added a YAML configuration file for managing SFTP host details and file paths.

Refactor SFTP host directory handling and update configs
Updated local_base_dir logic to dynamically include hostname, ensuring more flexible and standardized directory structures. Removed redundant `re` dependency and simplified database query by hardcoding the table name. Adjusted `plc.yaml` to align with the new configuration and cleaned up unnecessary fields for unused hosts.

Refactor PLC YAML to use shared credentials and port.
Introduced reusable variables for username, password, and port to reduce redundancy and simplify updates across SFTP host configurations. This improves maintainability and consistency in handling connection details.

Refactor SFTP host selection to use hostnames.
Replaced numeric selection with hostname-based input for improved clarity and usability. Removed redundant logic for enumerating hosts and validation of numeric inputs. Simplified user interaction by directly matching inputted hostnames.
